Crimson Wine Group, Ltd. Key Developments

Crimson Wine Group, Ltd., Annual General Meeting, Jul 22, 2016
May 10 16
Crimson Wine Group, Ltd., Annual General Meeting, Jul 22, 2016, at 10:00 Pacific Standard Time. Location: Pine Ridge Vineyards 5901 Silverado Trail Napa, CA 94558 United States Agenda: To elect seven members to Board of Directors; to ratify the selection of Moss Adams LLP as the independent registered public accounting firm of the company for the year ending December 31, 2016; and to transact such other business that may properly come before the annual meeting or any adjournment thereof.


Crimson Wine Group, Ltd. Appoints Francesca Schuler as Director
Mar 11 16
On March 11, 2016, the board of directors of Crimson Wine Group, Ltd. increased the number of directors constituting the Board from six to seven and appointed Francesca Schuler to be a director of the company, filling the vacancy, to hold office until the next annual meeting of stockholders. The Board has determined that Ms. Schuler is independent under the listing standards of the NASDAQ Stock Market. At the time of her appointment, the Board did not appoint Ms. Schuler to any committee of the Board. Ms. Schuler has over 20 years of experience leading and managing multi-channel businesses and has focused on brand strategy, portfolio management, product development and innovation, e-commerce and digital strategy, CRM, and sales. Ms. Schuler is currently the Chief Marketing Officer at In-Shape Health Clubs.


Crimson Wine Group, Ltd. Elimination of Natasha Hayes as Vice President of Marketing
Feb 22 16
Effective on February 16, 2016, as a result of a management restructuring of Crimson Wine Group, Ltd., the position of Vice President of Marketing has been eliminated and as a result, Natasha Hayes is no longer an employee of the company.


